HEADWORD: Swiple
<hw>Swi"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Swipe</er>.]</ety> <def>That part of a flail which strikes the grain
in thrashing; a swingel.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>swipel</asp>,
and <asp>swipple</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

